# Legend Website Project Rules

## Project Overview
Modern, responsive single-page website for Legendary Hustlers with clean, elegant design and excellent mobile experience.

## Tech Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 15.3.3 with TypeScript
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4
- **UI Components**: Custom components with Tailwind
- **Animations**: Framer Motion for parallax and scroll effects
- **Form Handling**: React Hook Form with file upload
- **Email**: EmailJS or similar for contact form
- **Payment**: Square integration for store
- **Images**: Next.js Image optimization

## Website Structure
### Single Page Sections (in order):
1. **Hero Section**: Looping video background with navigation
2. **Services Section**: Grid of service cards
3. **Contact Section**: Form with image upload capability
4. **About Us Section**: 4 team member cards

### Separate Pages:
- **Store Page**: Product cards with Square checkout integration

## Design Requirements
- **Mobile-first responsive design**
- **Clean, minimal aesthetic**
- **Modern typography**
- **Parallax scroll effects**
- **Smooth transitions**
- **No unnecessary logos or text**
- **Great navigation UX**

## Email Configuration
- Contact form sends to: office@legendaryhustlers.com
- Order confirmations to same email

## Development Phases
1. **Phase 1**: Foundation & aesthetic (current)
   - Basic structure and layout
   - Responsive design
   - Dummy content and images
   - Navigation system

2. **Phase 2**: Functionality
   - Contact form with image upload
   - Email integration
   - Form validation

3. **Phase 3**: Store Integration
   - Square payment system
   - Product management
   - Order processing

## Code Standards
- Use TypeScript for all components
- Follow Next.js 15 app router conventions
- Use Tailwind CSS for all styling
- Create reusable components
- Implement proper SEO tags
- Ensure accessibility (WCAG 2.1)

## Component Structure
```
src/
├── app/
│   ├── page.tsx (main single page)
│   ├── store/page.tsx (store page)
│   ├── layout.tsx
│   └── globals.css
├── components/
│   ├── ui/ (reusable UI components)
│   ├── sections/ (page sections)
│   ├── forms/ (form components)
│   └── store/ (store components)
├── lib/ (utilities)
└── types/ (TypeScript types)
```

